    {
      "text": "[CHARACTER CREATION - Start]\n\nYou've chosen to create a character for a frontier ranger campaign set in a ruined observatory on a stormy night.\n\n**Character Concept:** A practical ranger keeping watch at the frontier\n\n**Choose your creation method:**\n\n**Option 1: [AIGenerated]**\nI'll generate a complete character based on your concept - race, class, abilities, background, and equipment all created for you.\n\n**Option 2: [StandardDND]**\nTraditional step-by-step creation - choose your race, class, ability scores, background, and equipment using standard D&D 5e rules.\n\n**Option 3: [CustomClass]**\nDesign a completely custom class with unique features and abilities.\n\nWhich option would you like?",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 3
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "The storm lashes against the crumbling stone walls of the observatory, rain streaming through shattered skylights above. Lightning flashes illuminate the ancient brass instruments scattered across the floor\u2014twisted telescopes, cracked orrery gears, a massive meridian circle now lying in three pieces. Your watch post at the observatory's eastern archway offers a clear view of the frontier road below, though tonight the darkness swallows everything beyond thirty feet.\n\nThe wind carries the distant howl of something\u2014a wolf, perhaps, or something else that prowls the frontier. You've seen lights in the ruins before. Flickering, unnatural. The locals say they're ghosts of astronomers who died here when the College collapsed. You know better than to believe ghost stories, but you also know better than to ignore what you've seen.\n\nA sound echoes from below\u2014the scrape of metal on stone. Someone or something has breached the ground floor.",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Hold Position - Stay at the eastern archway, maintain the high ground, and wait for intruders to reveal themselves",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 5
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "You press yourself against the cold stone frame of the eastern archway, rain dripping from your brow as you peer into the darkness below. The storm masks some sounds, but your position grants you a clear sightline to the observatory's main chamber.\n\nThree figures move among the debris on the ground floor. Their silhouettes are wrong\u2014too hunched, too quick. One carries a torch that guttering flames, casting twisted shadows across the broken instruments. You catch fragments of their conversation:\n\n\"...find the signalman's sextant... worth twice your life...\"\n\nThey're scavengers. Or something worse pretending to be. The torchlight catches metal\u2014arms, not tools. The largest one Sports a jagged scar across its blocky head. Goblins, you realize. Frontier raiders, likely looking for shelter\u2014or prey.\n\nThey haven't seen you yet. The darkness and the rain are on your side. But the large one pauses, its piggish nose twitching. It smells something. Maybe the oil from your torch, maybe just the scent of a living human in the wet air.\n\nIt looks up toward the eastern archway.\n\n[PERCEPTION CHECK: 1d20+0 = 11] You can make out three goblins with crude weapons. The scarred one's suspicious but hasn't spotted you yet.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 6
    }
  ],
